@@ -77,4 +77,12 @@ Demo users are supplied only by an explicitly separate mock loader and never inv
 
 Focused frontend coverage fixes exact runtime validation, canonical endpoint selection, demo isolation, state/error mapping, retry transitions, and request-generation safeguards. Backend coverage fixes the exact serialized users-list response and unauthenticated 401 boundary without changing backend behavior. DEV-011 adds no writes, page redesign, dependency, legacy-client migration, or authorization change.
 
+## User Management profiles read-only slice (DEV-012)
+
+DEV-012 preserves the complete DEV-011 users slice and adds a second independent section to the registered `/admin` page. With demo mode disabled, it requests `GET /user-management/profiles` through the canonical authenticated client, producing `GET /api/v1/user-management/profiles`. Successful data must be an array whose objects contain exactly the `UserManagementProfileRead` fields: integer `id` and `user_id`; nullable strings `display_name`, `personnel_number`, `job_title`, `phone_number`, and `notes`; boolean `is_active`; and valid ISO datetime strings `created_at` and `updated_at`. Missing, mistyped, additional, or invalid datetime fields are rejected before UI state is updated.
+
+Profile demo records are supplied only through a separate mock loader and never call the backend. Profiles independently present loading, populated, empty, and retryable error states without coupling their result to the users section. Active 401 responses clear `pk_skdk_token` and navigate to `/login`; stale or unmounted 401 responses cannot clear the session or navigate. A 403 and malformed-response, network, configuration, server, unexpected, stale, and unmounted outcomes preserve the token. Generation invalidation prevents superseded or unmounted profile requests from changing current state.
+
+Focused frontend coverage fixes the exact runtime contract, canonical endpoint, demo isolation, error mapping, retry transitions, and request-generation safeguards. Backend coverage fixes the exact serialized profiles-list contract, nullable values, datetime serialization, and unauthenticated 401 boundary without changing backend business behavior or authorization. DEV-012 adds no writes, redesign, dependency, unrelated client migration, or backend behavior change.
+
 Operational prerequisites remain a migrated database with an active user, a valid CORS origin for the deployed frontend, secure HTTPS deployment, a supplied `VITE_API_URL`, and demo mode disabled outside intentional demos. Automated coverage does not replace a manual deployed-browser check with a real backend session.
